{"priority": "major", "kind": "bug", "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/haptix-tools.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/haptix-tools"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{64458fe2-275f-452c-8055-1c7293538e54}ts=default"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "haptix-tools", "full_name": "osrf/haptix-tools", "uuid": "{64458fe2-275f-452c-8055-1c7293538e54}"}, "links": {"attachments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/haptix-tools/issues/2/attachments_page=1.json"}, "self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/haptix-tools/issues/2.json"}, "watch": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/haptix-tools/issues/2/watch"}, "comments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/haptix-tools/issues/2/comments_page=1.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/haptix-tools/issues/2/allow-to-shutdown-windows-running-on-the"}, "vote": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/haptix-tools/issues/2/vote"}}, "reporter": {"display_name": "Carlos Ag\u00fcero", "uuid": "{da8a8e89-4bb0-421b-bd0e-dbbed3d4ed6a}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bda8a8e89-4bb0-421b-bd0e-dbbed3d4ed6a%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bda8a8e89-4bb0-421b-bd0e-dbbed3d4ed6a%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/692bf15758111acaddae4da15a47f9e5d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsCA-0.png"}}, "nickname": "caguero", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:4ded1ddf-947e-4154-bbd1-3dba24f1bdbd"}, "title": "Allow to shutdown Windows running on the virtual machine", "component": null, "votes": 0, "watches": 1, "content": {"raw": "We should come up with a mechanism for allowing a clean shutdown of the Windows running in the virtual machine.\r\n\r\nWe should probably add a rule to the upstart job for stopping the service during shutdown. We could also add a `post-stop` rule that tells Windows to shutdown (using `net rpc`?).\r\n\r\nReference: http://blog.joshsoftware.com/2012/02/14/upstart-scripts-in-ubuntu/", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>We should come up with a mechanism for allowing a clean shutdown of the Windows running in the virtual machine.</p>\n<p>We should probably add a rule to the upstart job for stopping the service during shutdown. We could also add a <code>post-stop</code> rule that tells Windows to shutdown (using <code>net rpc</code>?).</p>\n<p>Reference: <a href=\"http://blog.joshsoftware.com/2012/02/14/upstart-scripts-in-ubuntu/\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">http://blog.joshsoftware.com/2012/02/14/upstart-scripts-in-ubuntu/</a></p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": null, "state": "new", "version": null, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2015-02-24T01:43:58.765496+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2015-02-24T01:43:58.765496+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 2}